		{
			"name": "🟠 OAUTH2 Mode",
			"description": "Generic OIDC provider with flat JWT claims.\n\nSet `security.auth-mode=OAUTH2` in application.properties.\n\n**How it differs from KEYCLOAK mode:**\n- Reads roles from a flat `roles` claim (not nested `realm_access.roles`)\n- Reads permissions from a flat `permissions` claim\n- Claim names are configurable via `security.oauth2.*` properties\n\n**Testing with Keycloak tokens:**\nSince Keycloak nests roles in `realm_access`, OAUTH2 mode will see empty roles/permissions.\nThis demonstrates why KEYCLOAK mode exists.\n\n**For real OAUTH2 testing**, use an IdP that puts roles in flat claims (Auth0, Okta with custom rules), or add a Keycloak protocol mapper that copies realm_access.roles to a flat `roles` claim.\n\n**Configurable claims:**\n```\nsecurity.oauth2.username-claim=preferred_username\nsecurity.oauth2.user-id-claim=sub\nsecurity.oauth2.roles-claim=roles\nsecurity.oauth2.permissions-claim=permissions\n```",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Get Token from OIDC Provider",
					"description": "Using Keycloak as an example OIDC provider.\nReplace with your IdP's token endpoint for production use.",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }],
						"body": {
							"mode": "urlencoded",
							"urlencoded": [
								{ "key": "client_id",  "value": "{{keycloak_client_id}}" },
								{ "key": "grant_type", "value": "password" },
								{ "key": "username",   "value": "alice" },
								{ "key": "password",   "value": "alice123" }
							]
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{keycloak_url}}/realms/{{keycloak_realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
							"host": ["{{keycloak_url}}"],
							"path": ["realms", "{{keycloak_realm}}", "protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
						}
					},
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('OIDC token obtained', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"    var json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set('alice_token', json.access_token);",
									"});"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "GET /me — flat claims extraction",
					"description": "With Keycloak tokens: username ✅ (preferred_username), userId ✅ (sub), roles [] (nested in realm_access), permissions [] (no flat claim).\n\nWith Auth0/Okta: all fields populated if custom claims are configured.",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{alice_token}}" }],
						"url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["me"] }
					},
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('OAUTH2 extracts username and userId from flat claims', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"    var json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(json.username).to.be.a('string');",
									"    pm.expect(json.userId).to.be.a('string');",
									"    // With Keycloak tokens, roles will be empty (nested structure)",
									"    // With a flat-claim IdP, roles would be populated",
									"});"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "POST /posts — roles empty → 403",
					"description": "Demonstrates that OAUTH2 mode with Keycloak tokens can't find roles (they're nested). This is why KEYCLOAK mode exists.",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{alice_token}}" },
